lore: Debris fragments damaged Jek Porkins' X-wing, causing a cascade of computer and flight control failures.
name: I've Got A Problem Here

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on a starship with a [Nav Computer] or astromech aboard. Target [Nav computer] or astromech and draw destiny. If destiny > 1, astromech lost (lose Effect) or [Nav Computer] is canceled (may add 1 astromech); otherwise, Effect lost.
lore: "WHAAAAAAAAAOOOOW!"
name: I've Lost Artoo!

gametext: Use 1 Force to prevent any character or starship just deployed by the opponent from battling or moving for the remainder of this turn.
lore: As is often the case with a hasty plan, a quick heroic escape from the Death Star was temporarily thwarted by the magnetically sealed door in the trash compactor.
name: Imperial Barrier

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your warrior. May target a character, creature or vehicle using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny > defense value.
lore: A BlasTech DH-17 blaster pistol. Uses power packs and high-energy blaster gases. Shoots bolts of explosive coherent light energy.
name: Imperial Blaster

gametext: If any Imperial leader is present with a Scomp link, you may: Glance at the cards in any Reserve Deck for 20 seconds. Shuffle, cut and replace. OR If also at a Death Star site, cancel Scomp Link Access or Into The Garbage Chute, Flyboy.
lore: Imperial officers are issued coded cylinders which access computer information via Scomp links. Each cylinder is coded to the officer's own security clearance.
name: Imperial Code Cylinder

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots.
lore: Among the Empire's best pilots. Loyal and fearless. Use superior numbers to overwhelm opponents. Trained under combat conditions. Wear sealed, high-gravity flight suits.
name: Imperial Pilot

gametext: If opponent has more total characters and starships on table than you have, use 1 Force to draw destiny. Retrieve that number of Stormtroopers and/or TIE/lns.
lore: Imperial stormtroopers deploy in 8-10 trooper squads. Reinforcements are typically held in reserve according to standard Imperial operating procedures.
name: Imperial Reinforcements

characteristics: \b Death Star trooper\b0, trooper guard, \b trooper\b0
gametext: Power +4 when defending a battle. Cannot move.
lore: Elite soldiers trained in combat techniques and weapons skills. Death Star trooper Tajis Durmin is typical of those assigned to guard key areas of the Death Star.
name: Imperial Trooper Guard

gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.
lore: Mainstay of Imperial Navy. 1.6 kilometers long. Has hangars and facilities for TIE fighter squadrons, shuttles, drop-ships and combat vehicles such as AT-ATs and AT-ATs.
name: Imperial-Class Star Destroyer

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your Star Destroyer. May target a starship using 1 Force. Draw destiny. If destiny +2 > defense value, all starship weapons deployed on target are lost, armor or maneuver = 0 and hyperspeed = 0.
lore: Fires blasts of ionized energy. Causes massive disruptions in weapon, engine and computer systems aboard a target. Disables starship defenses against tractor beams.
name: Ion Cannon

gametext: If It Could Be Worse was just played, it is canceled and you may use X Force to raise damage against opponent by X amount. OR If opponent just lost Force from a battle, play to increase loss by 1 Force.
lore: Things went from bad to worse when Luke was attacked by a dianoga, a parasitic predator native to the planet Vodran.
name: It's Worse

gametext: * To deploy, requires 1 Force from each players' Force Pile. Cannot deploy otherwise. Deploy only on Tatooine, but may move elsewhere.
lore: Small, rodent-like scavenger species. Refurbish and sell droids. Nest in sandcrawlers. Considered to be pests by most species.
name: Jawa

gametext: To deploy (on your side of table), requires 3 Force from both players' Force Piles. Cannot deploy otherwise. All your Jawas are forfeit +1.
lore: Jawas travel in packs for protection. They use ambush tactics against unwary droids in the canyons of the Jundland Wastes. "Aeeeyaa!"
name: Jawa Pack

gametext: Deploy on any alien if Cantina, Mos Eisley or Jabba's Sail Barge on table. That alien may not use ability in battles (if Kabe, she also cannot 'steal'). Utinni Effect canceled by moving that alien to one of those sites without 'driving' a vehicle.
lore: Popular beverage served in many cantinas and tapcafes. Has intoxicating effect on many species. Favorite drink of Kabe, Chadra-Fan thief of Mos Eisley.
name: Juri Juice

dark_side_text: Your starships deploy -1 here, -2 if Tarkin is aboard a starship here. If you control, Kessel Run is canceled.
gametext: Total ability of 6 or more required for you to draw battle destiny here.   Your starships deploy -1 here, -2 if Tarkin is aboard a starship here. If you control, Kessel Run is canceled.
light_side_text: Total ability of 6 or more required for you to draw battle destiny here.
name: Kessel

gametext: Deploy on your non-warrior character (except droids) to give that character warrior ([Warrior]) skill. OR Deploy on your warrior. That character is power +1. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: Assassins are highly valued by Jabba the Hutt and other gangsters. Ket Maliss, Prince Xizor's "shadow killer," has unknown but undoubtably lethal business in Mos Eisley.
name: Ket Maliss

gametext: If opponent just forfeited or lost a character, use 1 Force to regenerate one of your own characters. Retrieve the character closest to the top of your Lost Pile into your hand.
lore: A \b dejarik\b0  of a ferocious creature with incredible healing abilities. Extinct on their homeworld of Kintan, but used as a guard beasts by many Hutt gangsters.
name: Kintan Strider

gametext: Immediately lost if at same site as overprotective mother, Kal'Falnl C'ndros. Cannot board starfighters or enclosed vehicles.
lore: A female insectoid Yam'rii. Very strong and easily angered. Known for stealth, but also has good technological aptitude. Meat eater. Loves eggs.
name: Kitik Keed'kak

gametext: At any time during your turn, may use 1 Force to 'defuse' (lose) any one mine at same site.
lore: Armored military droid which specializes in laying explosive mines. Originally intended to set charges inside ore and spice mines, but has also been converted for military use.
name: LIN-V8M (Elleyein-Veeateemm)

characteristics: \b Black Sun agent\b0, \b information broker\b0, \b spy\b0
gametext: Once each turn, during your control phase, you may reveal the top card of your Reserve Deck to both players. If it is a vehicle or starship, card is immediately lost. Otherwise, return it to the top of your Reserve Deck, Force Pile or Used Pile.
lore: \b Information broker\b0. \b Spy\b0. Devaronian males instinctively have 'wanderlust.' Frustrated that he must be reclusive due to shady past. Suffers from prejudice due to devilish appearance.
name: Labria

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on an interior sire. May target a seeker (use defense value = 1), character or creature for free. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny -1 > defense value. Laser Projector may be targeted by any weapon (use defense value = 1).
lore: Laser system activated by distress signal from guards. Used at security checkpoints and detention block control rooms. Targeting guided by centralized droid controller.
name: Laser Projector

gametext: Deploy on any system. Target an opponent's starship. Target's power and forfeit = 0. When target reaches Utinni Effect, target draws one destiny. Utinni Effect canceled if destiny > 2. Otherwise, draw again next move phase, etc.
lore: Starships can become damaged in combat and rendered ineffective until they can be repaired and re-outfitted.
name: Lateral Damage

gametext: Deploy -1 for starship weapons of any starship he pilots. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Subtracts 1 from maneuver of any starfighter he pilots.
lore: Former fighter pilot grounded after injury. Tactical officer aboard Death Star. Competent strategist. Specializes in directing Imperial starfighters.
name: Lieutenant Tanbris

gametext: May carry 4 passengers. Deploy and move only at interior mobile sites. May move without presence aboard. Also, may move as a 'react' only to a battle or Force drain (if within range).
lore: System of \b enclosed\b0  high-speed vertical and horizontal transport cylinders. Used in space stations, large starships, Death Stars, etc.
name: Lift Tube

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your warrior. If your power droid or fusion generator present, may target a character, creature or vehicle using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny +1 > defense value. May fire repeatedly for 2 Force each time.
lore: BlasTech model T-21 light repeating blaster. Excellent power, good range. Carries energy for 25 shots. Unlimited firepower when attached to a power generator.
name: Light Repeating Blaster Rifle

gametext: If the opponent has two cards or less in hand, opponent must immediately lose 2 Force (4 Force if it is your turn). If the opponent has Fusion Generator Supply Tanks aboard a starship, loss is reduced by 2.
lore: The Empire dominates consumption of resources. Despite being efficient, Rebel logistical and maintenance officers often are compelled to expend emergency reserves.
name: Limited Resources

gametext: Use 1 Force at the beginning of your battle phase to allow any two of your Stormtroopers in the Cantina to battle any one opponent's character (your choice). You may add one battle destiny. No other battles may occur in Cantina this turn.
lore: "Looks like somebody's beginning to take an interest in your handiwork." Imperial stormtroopers coerce local residents to assist them in the apprehension of Rebel scum.
name: Local Trouble

gametext: If your pilot (or permanent pilot) is defending a battle alone at a system or sector, add one battle destiny. OR If Motti is defending a battle alone at a system or sector, add two battle destiny.
lore: One lone TIE fighter, acting as a scout near the Death Star, suddenly encountered the \ul Millennium Falcon\ul0.
name: Lone Pilot

gametext: If any warrior is defending a battle alone at a site, add one battle destiny. OR If Tagge is defending a battle alone at a site, add two battle destiny.
lore: Though generally deployed in squads, all Imperial warriors are trained in the close combat techniques and have a reputation for ferocity when cornered.
name: Lone Warrior

gametext: Use 1 Force to search through the opponent's Used Pile and move any droids you find there to opponent's Lost Pile. OR Use X Force to destroy any one droid on table where X = droid's deploy cost.
lore: Trooper 1124, Davin Felth, discovered droid plating dropped by R2-D2 and C-3PO when exiting escape pod.
name: Look Sir, Droids

gametext: Deploys for 1 Force to an unoccupied site. Deploys and moves like an undercover spy. When present with Luke of ability < 4 or pilot of ability < 3, choose one to be immediately lost (treat as an "all cards" situation). Seeker is also lost.
lore: Military version of a 'remote.' Programmed to stalk specific targets or secondary targets. Heat and light sensors track with fatal accuracy. Can stow away on starships.
name: Luke Seeker

gametext: Deploy on any Tatooine site. Target any Rebel. Target is power and forfeit -1 (-3 if target is Luke). If Rebel's forfeit reaches zero, Rebel is lost. Utinni Effect canceled when reached by target.
lore: "All right. I'll be right there, Aunt Beru."
name: Luke? Luuuuke!

gametext: Once during each of your control phases, may reveal opponent's hand by using X Force, where X = number of cards in opponent's hand. All unique (*) male Rebels and unique (*) male aliens there are lost.
lore: Female H'nemthe, a species whose females ritually kill their mates. Stranded on Tatooine due to questionable passage tax. Razor-sharp tongue. M'iiyoom means, 'nightlilly.'
name: M'iiyoom Onith

gametext: Landspeed = 3. Deploys to same site as a character targeted by a Utinni Effect (except Kessel Run). If this droid 'reaches' Utinni Effect, may relocate it here. Upon delivery, 'mouse' droid returns to your hand.
lore: Nicknamed for rodent-like appearance. Delivers orders and sensitive documents. Retractable manipulator arms. Made by Rebaxan Colmuni. Easily frightened.
name: MSE-6 'Mouse' Droid

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy near opponent's Reserve Deck. At any time, you may use 1 Force to peek at the top card of that deck. If "nighttime conditions" exist anywhere on table, you may peek at the top three cards.
lore: Electrobinocular view. Readouts list object's true and relative azimuth, elevation and range. Built-in night vision.
name: Macroscan

gametext: Deploy on your side of table. For each unit of ability you have present during a battle, you may use 1 Force to raise your total power by 1. Ability used in this way cannot also be used to draw destiny.
lore: Creature in \b dejarik\b0  hologame drawn from Alderaanian mythology. Stories describe molators as powerful, enchanted protectors of Alderaanian kings and queens.
name: Molator

gametext: If Tarkin is defending a battle alone, add two battle destiny. OR If any alien is defending a battle alone, add one battle destiny.
lore: A ruthless ruler of Outer Rim Territories, Grand Moff Tarkin used the Death Star to destroy Alderaan, creating the doctrine of rule by fear.
name: Moment Of Triumph

gametext: Power +1 if present with Lirin Car'n or any bounty hunter. If lost or forfeited as a result of a battle, Myo 'regenerates' (place on top of your Used Pile).
lore: A regenerating, primitive, violent, desert dwelling, fearless, mercenary-joining Lirin Car'n-befriending, cyclopian Abyssin from Byss. Calling him 'monoc' will start a fight.
name: Myo

gametext: If both players have a spy at same site, draw destiny. Add 2 if opponent's spy is Undercover. Opponent's spy is lost if destiny > 2.
lore: Immense Ranat scavenger from Aralia. Slyly spies for anyone willing to pay his price. Outcast. Works as a laborer for Hrchek, the Saurin droid trader.
name: Nevar Yalnal

gametext: Deploy on a site. Adds 1 to the total weapon destiny of each of your automated weapons at same or adjacent sites. During battle, may add the power of one of your characters at an adjacent site you control to your total.
lore: Remote surveillance viewers with droid controllers supplement security. Can activate alarms and automated weapons when needed, bringing help to endangered locations.
name: Observation Holocam

gametext: Shuffle any player's Reserve Deck or Lost Pile or Used Pile.
lore: Difficult-to-play instrument which enhances music. Tech Mo'r plays one for Figrin D'an and the Modal Nodes in the Mos Eisley Cantina.
name: Ommni Box

gametext: Deploy on any Yavin 4 site. Target one Imperial. When Imperial reaches target site, 'steal' necklace. Whenever necklace is present during Force drain: add 1 to Force drain and may then pass (for free) to an adjacent site you control (if any), and so on.
lore: Necklace worn by Princess Leia during the awards ceremony after the Battle of Yavin. A powerful artifact in the Alderaanian royal family for dozens of generations.
name: Organa's Ceremonial Necklace

gametext: Target any weapon (except a Gaderffii Stick or any Ewok weapon). Draw destiny. Weapon lost if destiny < weapon's destiny number. If destiny = 0, the character or starship carrying weapon is also lost.
lore: Weapons like lightsabers, turbolasers and blasters run on powerful energy cells or generators. Occasionally, these cells overheat causing the weapon to unexpectedly explode.
name: Overload

gametext: Cause one Rebel Trooper to be immediately lost. OR If a Dark Jedi is present at a battle you have just won, use 1 Force to attempt to choke any opposing character present. Draw destiny. If destiny > target's ability, target is lost.
lore: Darth Vader often used physical means of 'persuasion' to get information. Captain Antilles of \ul Tantive IV\ul0  chose to die rather than reveal the location of the stolen Death Star plans.
name: Physical Choke

gametext: Power +3 when battling at same site as Dr. Evazan, unless opponent has a lightsaber present. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots.
lore: A male Quara (or fingered Aqualish). Thug, \b smuggler\b0  and partner of Dr. Evazan. Has a poor quality cybernetic arm replacement.
name: Ponda Baba

gametext: During a battle, target opponent's character or vehicle present with two (or more) of your weapons. Add all weapon destiny draws together. Apply that total separately for each weapon in an order of your choosing.
lore: "Only Imperial stormtroopers are so precise."
name: Precise Attack

gametext: Deploy on any location to add one (Dark Side Force icon) icon and one (Light Side Force icon) icon.
lore: "A location is affected by the history of the events which occur there. The Force "...binds the galaxy together" and has an ebb and flow."
name: Presence Of The Force

gametext: If you initiate a battle where present, you must predict the winner before the battle starts. If correct, randomly retrieve one lost card. If incorrect, lose 1 Force. Immune to attrition < 3.
lore: Renowned female psychic. Predictor of doom. Agent for Governor Aryon of Tatooine. Tailed Jabba and his thugs to Docking Bay 94 when they confronted Han Solo.
name: Prophetess

gametext: When aboard a capital starship, adds 1 to power and hyperspeed, and that starship is immune to attrition < 3. Too large to go aboard a starfighter.
lore: Typical of the old model astromechs still used on capital starships and large freighters. Has armored Mark II reactor drone shell. R1-G4 was abandoned after owner was captured.
name: R1-G4 (Arone-Geefour)

gametext: While aboard a non-creature vehicle, adds 1 to power, maneuver and landspeed. May drive transport vehicles.
lore: Typical multiple-use droid. Controls and repairs vehicles and computers. R4-M9 was once used by the Empire to pull data from Tantive IV's computer banks.
name: R4-M9 (Arfour-Emmnine)

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your side of table. During your control phase, you may return any cards from your hand to the top of your Used Pile.
lore: The Death Star has many terminals coupled to the main reactor for power distribution throughout the immense space station.
name: Reactor Terminal

gametext: Deploy on any droid at any site. Droid cannot move and cannot utilize its "game text." During your deploy phase, Restraining Bolt may be transferred (for free) to another droid at same site.
lore: Affixed to droid's special recessed socket by using a fusion welder. Bolts can override a droid's circuits, freezing it in place if the droid tries to disobey orders.
name: Restraining Bolt

gametext: Deploys only to a Tatooine site. May add 1 driver and 7 passengers. Cannot move to mobile sites. Adds 1 to forfeit of each Jawa at same exterior site.
lore: Warren-like \b enclosed\b0  homes for Jawa tribes. Protect against Tusken Raiders, krayt dragons, etc. 36 meters longs, 17 meters tall. Originally mining vehicles. No two look alike.
name: Sandcrawler

gametext: Use 1 Force to glance at the cards in the opponent's hand for 10 seconds. You may move any one Rebel you find there to the top of opponent's Used Pile.
lore: Imperials use sensitive equipment to search captured ships for shielded compartments. Scanning crew BT-445 planned to search the \ul Millennium Falcon\ul0.
name: Scanning Crew

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any Tatooine site (except docking bay). Target any trooper on Death Star. When target reaches Utinni Effect, attrition +1 against opponent in all Tatooine battles as long as target remains at same site as Utinni Effect.
lore: Vader sent Imperial stormtroopers to the surface of Tatooine in search of the stolen Death Star plans. "There'll be no one to stop us this time."
name: Send A Detachment Down

gametext: Cancel one Interrupt (or one 'react') by drawing a destiny < ability of your highest-ability character on table. OR Cancel one Alter card just played.
lore: "I sense something. A presence I've not felt since..."
name: Sense

gametext: Use 2 Force to target one opponent's character. Draw destiny. If destiny > character's ability, character immediately returns to opponent's hand. (Also, any cards deployed on character return to owners' hands.)
lore: "...bring me the passengers. I want them alive!" Imperial soldiers use blaster stun settings to intimidate or to capture prisoners for questioning and interrogation.
name: Set For Stun

gametext: Deploys free to same site as one of your Imperials with ability > 2.
lore: One of the countless elite shock troops totally loyal to the Emperor. Unquestioningly follows orders. Willing to sacrifice their lives to accomplish a mission. First-strike force.
name: Stormtrooper

gametext: Deploy on your trooper. May use any number of weapons and devices. Trooper is immune to attrition < 3 when at a planet site.
lore: Standard-issue Imperial equipment with full survival and encampment gear, storage, plus ammunition and food for an extended deployment. Makes each trooper self-sufficient.
name: Stormtrooper Backpack

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on any Imperial or alien. Character's power and forfeit are +1. If on Death Star, power and forfeit are +2.
lore: Standard Imperial issue for stormtroopers. Contains grappling hook, rope, and other miscellaneous emergency tools. Rebels have been known to steal and use them.
name: Stormtrooper Utility Belt

gametext: Deploy on any planet system to cause "nighttime conditions" at related sites. During battles there, both sides add one destiny to power only. Spies deploy free to sites under "nighttime conditions."
lore: When the twin suns of Tatooine set. "Sand People or worse" become a threat, and battles are more dangerous. On Hoth, temperatures drop to deadly extremes.
name: Sunsdown

gametext: Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.
lore: TIE advanced x1 fighter boasting improved power plant, stronger shields, armored hull and enhanced weapons. Deployed to elite Imperial Navy pilots.
name: TIE Advanced x1

gametext: Deploy -1 to same system as any Imperial capital starship. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.
lore: TIE or Twin Ion Engine. TIE/ln model is Empire's most common fighter. Quick and maneuverable. Solar-panel wings supplement power generator. Built by Sienar Fleet Systems.
name: TIE Fighter

gametext: May add 1 Pilot and 1 passenger, or 2 passengers. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.
lore: Limited production, light reconnaissance starship. Minimal armor and weapons. Long-range sensor and communications array. Scouts for Rebel activity.
name: TIE Scout

gametext: Deploy on any Yavin 4 site immediately after winning a battle elsewhere. Target a warrior involved in that battle. Target's power and forfeit are -2 (-3 if Leia) until target reaches this Utinni Effect (which is then canceled).
lore: Sophisticated communication equipment hidden in the ruins of the extinct Massassi race is used to coordinate forces and to re-call Rebel officers for debriefing and orders.
name: Tactical Re-Call

gametext: If both players just drew one battle destiny, use 1 Force to switch numbers.
lore: Takeel, a burned-out Snivvian mercenary known as a double-crosser. Spice addicted. Frequents the Cantina looking for work, but has also turned lawbreakers over to the Empire.
name: Takeel

gametext: Target two starfighters (your TIE/ln and any Rebel starfighter) present at same system or sector. Each player draws destiny. Opponent totals destiny and starship's power. You total destiny, TIE's power and TIE's maneuver. Lowest total loses starfighter.
lore: Maneuver named after Adar Tallon, tactician of the Old Republic who revolutionized starfighter combat. Pursuing fighter rolls and turns, maintaining speed and target lock.
name: Tallon Roll

dark_side_text: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Tatooine sites.
gametext: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Tatooine sites.   If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Tatooine sites.
light_side_text: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Tatooine sites.
name: Tatooine

dark_side_text: Your aliens here, except Tusken Raiders, are each power +1.
gametext: Your aliens here are each forfeit +1.   Your aliens here, except Tusken Raiders, are each power +1.
light_side_text: Your aliens here are each forfeit +1.
name: Tatooine: Cantina

dark_side_text: Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.
gametext: Your docking bay transit from here requires 2 Force.   Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.
light_side_text: Your docking bay transit from here requires 2 Force.
name: Tatooine: Docking Bay 94

dark_side_text: Your Jawas deploy here for 1 Force from you only.
gametext: All your Jawas are power and forfeit -1 here.   Your Jawas deploy here for 1 Force from you only.
light_side_text: All your Jawas are power and forfeit -1 here.
name: Tatooine: Jawa Camp

dark_side_text: Your Tusken Raiders here are each forfeit +1. If you control, Force drain +1 here.
gametext: Total ability of 6 or more required for you to draw battle destiny here.   Your Tusken Raiders here are each forfeit +1. If you control, Force drain +1 here.
light_side_text: Total ability of 6 or more required for you to draw battle destiny here.
name: Tatooine: Jundland Wastes

dark_side_text: Add 1 to each of your weapon destiny draws here. If you control, Force drain +1 here.
gametext: Add 1 to each of your weapon destiny draws here. If you control, Force drain +1 here.
name: Tatooine: Lars' Moisture Farm

dark_side_text: Your spies, thieves, bounty hunters and smugglers are each power and forfeit +1 here.
gametext: Your spies, thieves, bounty hunters and smugglers are each power and forfeit +1 here.
name: Tatooine: Mos Eisley

gametext: If Vader and Obi-Wan are present at same site, use 1 Force to initiate a duel between them. Compare their power, and add 2 if that character is armed with a lightsaber. Loser (lowest total) of duel is placed out of play.
lore: Vader and Obi-Wan Kenobi fought a final lightsaber duel near Hangar Bay 327 on the Death Star. "When I left you I was but the learner; now I am the master."
name: The Circle Is Now Complete

gametext: If Vader, Tarkin, Motti or Tagge is lost, use 2 Force to retrieve one of them from the Lost Pile. OR Use 4 Force to search through your Reserve Deck and take Vader, Tarkin, Motti, or Tagge into your hand. Shuffle deck, cut and replace.
lore: "No star system will dare oppose the Emperor now."
name: The Empire's Back

gametext: Deploy on opponent's side at same site as one of your mining droids. 'Explodes' at beginning of your next turn. Draw destiny. That number of opponent's characters there are immediately lost (owner's choice). Timer Mine is also lost.
lore: A timer-activated explosive device designed to be placed by a mining droid. Originally used in ore and spice mines for demolition. Altered for military applications.
name: Timer Mine

gametext: Twice during each of your control phases, may use 2 Force to draw 2 destiny for 2 chances at a destiny = 2. If successful, may steal or destroy up to 2 weapons or 2 devices present.
lore: Twins. \b Thieves\b0. Con artists. \b Spies\b0. Swindlers. Double agents. Brea and Senni use their natural charm to sway the unwary on the fringe of society.
name: Tonnika Sisters

gametext: If there are cards in the opponent's Used Pile during your battle phase, draw one destiny. All cards there with the same destiny number are lost.
lore: A Stennes Shifter, a near-human race. Have ability to blend unnoticed into crowds. Trinto profits from turning lawbreakers over to Imperial authorities.
name: Trinto Duaba

gametext: Select one of your troopers in a battle to make a 'charge.' If that trooper is a Death Star Trooper, it is power +3 the battle. If any other trooper, power +2. However, that trooper must be forfeited at end of battle.
lore: Imperial troopers are fearless and totally indoctrinated. Backed by the most powerful weapons and starships in the galaxy, they tend to consider themselves invincible.
name: Trooper Charge

gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on your Star Destroyer or any mobile system. May target a starship using 2 Force. Draw two destiny. Subtract 2 if targeting a capital starship. Otherwise, subtract 5. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
lore: High-powered blasters. Require power generators, cryogenic cooling units and large crews. More effective against capital starships than starfighters.
name: Turbolaser Battery

gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. Power + 1 if another non-unique Tusken Raider present. If you have four or more non-unique Tusken Raiders present, your total power here is +2.
lore: "Sand People." Ride banthas. Wield gaderffi (gaffi) sticks. Wear eye protectors and breath masks. Violent, nomadic, desert survival experts. "Urrrg! Ur Ur Uur!"
name: Tusken Raider

gametext: Use 1 Force to draw destiny. If destiny < the number of Tusken Raiders on table, you may scavenge (search through) the opponent's Used Pile. All vehicles, weapons or devices you find there are lost.
lore: "Sand People always ride single file to hide their numbers." They frequently attack strangers as they scavenge for useful equipment. Looted Luke's landspeeder.
name: Tusken Scavengers

gametext: May add 1 driver and 2 passengers. May move as a 'react.'
lore: \b Enclosed\b0  repulsorlift landspeeder. Micro-thrusters placed around spherical hull. Seats three. Extremely maneuverable. Top speed of 160 km per hour.
name: Ubrikkian 9000 Z001

gametext: If one of your Jawas is at the same location as any Utinni Effect, 'steal' that Utinni Effect into your hand, to use or lose as your own. OR Cancel any Interrupt or Effect with 'Jawa' in the card name.
lore: The Jawa who shot R2-D2 with an ionization gun called to his companions, "Utinni!", the Jawa word for "come here!"
name: Utinni!

gametext: May add 1 pilot. If Vader is pilot, Custom TIE is immune to attrition < 4.
lore: TIE advanced x1 prototype. First of a limited production run leading to the development of the TIE Interceptor. At Vader's insistence a hyperdrive was installed.
name: Vader's Custom TIE

gametext: If Vader is defending a battle alone at a site, add 1 to power and add one battle destiny. OR If any other Imperial with ability > 2 is defending a battle alone at a site, add one battle destiny.
lore: Darth Vader's armored mask and life-support system provide him with extraordinary physical protection in duels and battles, in addition to his Dark Jedi combat skill.
name: Vader's Eye

gametext: Deploy on Vader. May add 1 to Force drain where present. May target a character or creature for free. Draw two destiny. Target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if total destiny > defense value.
lore: Custom-built by Darth Vader. After the Clone Wars, he wielded this weapon while hunting down the last of the Jedi. Cuts through almost anything except another lightsaber blade.
name: Vader's Lightsaber

gametext: Adds immunity to attrition < 2 to all your vehicles and droids at same location. Also, if 'treadwell' droid is at a docking bay, adds immunity to attrition < 3 to all your starfighters at the related system and related sectors.
lore: Standard treadwell droid. This one, also known as 'Eyesixsixtoo', is typical of the thousands of droids which repair and maintain heavy machinery and starfighters.
name: WED15-I662 'Treadwell' Droid

gametext: Everything in Trash Compactor is crushed (Lost).
lore: Trash compactors crush waste before it is jettisoned into space. Magnetically sealed to prevent leakage. R2-D2 saved the day by shutting down compactor 3263827.
name: We're All Gonna Be A Lot Thinner!

gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on opponent's side of table. All opponent's warriors are deploy +1.
lore: Imperial troopers use tactics to strand and cut off fugitives. Only daring and unpredictable actions gave Luke and Leia a chance to escape.
name: Wrong Turn

gametext: If at the beginning of your control phase any weapons or droids are present at same site, all of them are lost. If in the Cantina, all weapons and droids there are immediately lost.
lore: Gruff, surly, no-blasters-allowed bartender. Hates droids. "We don't serve their kind here." Wants to concoct the perfect drink for Jabba so he can work as his personal bartender.
name: Wuher

dark_side_text: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Yavin 4 sites.
gametext: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Yavin 4 sites.   If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Yavin 4 sites.
light_side_text: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Yavin 4 sites.
name: Yavin 4

dark_side_text: Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.
gametext: Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.   Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.
light_side_text: Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.
name: Yavin 4: Docking Bay

dark_side_text: An Imperial alone here battles at power +2 and is immune to attrition.
gametext: An Imperial alone here battles at power +2 and is immune to attrition.
name: Yavin 4: Jungle

gametext: If an opponent has just initiated a battle, triple the resulting battle damage for the eventual loser. OR Triple the result of Don't Underestimate Our Chances.
lore: "Evacuate? In our moment of triumph?"
name: You Overestimate Their Chances

gametext: Deploy beside either player's Lost Pile. That pile is turned face down. Cards from that player's Life Force may not be viewed when they are lost.
lore: "With this blast shield down, I can't even see. How am I supposed to fight?"
name: Your Eyes Can Deceive You

gametext: During any battle involving both Vader and Obi-Wan, you may add one battle destiny. OR Destroy (cancel) either: Return Of A Jedi, Jedi Lightsaber, Jedi Presence or Old Ben.
lore: "You should not have come back."
name: Your Powers Are Weak, Old Man
